Maine is kinda like a sore wiener… So good to be back in vacation land!

node.text: The bigs bite at night! Had seen this fish multiple times on my graph throughout the day yesterday. At first she wouldn’t jump at the sight of a dropshot, Swimbait, or a crank. After working on some other brush piles I decided to revisit the tree this fish was hanging. The sun was setting and I had made the switch to a 10” @googanbaits Mondo worm. Sure enough first cast on the drop, this fish crushed it. It amazes me how a little change in light or weather is enough to turn a stubborn fish into a killer. This is definitely a catch I won’t forget.

node.text: After hours of dropshottin and cranking finally found an ole girtha. Sometimes embracing the swamp ass and sunburnt nose is worth it.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Jonathan Barzacchini in St. Clair Shores, Michigan. May be an image of 1 person and outdoors.

node.text: Getting tossed by mega waves, and drifting through Uber schools of perch.. it’s what St. Clair is all about. Very tough but fun couple of days on this big bodacious lake. One of my favorite things ever is learning a new fishery and chasing smallmouth in the process.

node.text: It has been a smallmouth filled week up here in Maine. @grant_langmore7 and I  have chased down stripers, fished 7 different lakes and competed in the second Maine derb of the season all in a matter of a few days. I know I’ve been lacking on the uploads but just know the best is coming. Thank you wieners for being patient 🙏🏻
